<DOC><DOCNO> AP890825-0205 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-08-25-89 0205EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r f PM-ATandamp;T-GE-ABC     08-25 0139</FIRST><SECOND>PM-ATandamp;T-GE-ABC,0145</SECOND><HEAD>ATandamp;T Signs Satellite Deals With GE, ABC</HEAD><DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   American Telephone andamp; Telegraph Co. says it haschosen General Electric Co. to build its next generation ofcommunications satellites, and said ABC will use them to delivernetwork television programming.   The ATandamp;T contract with GE Astro-Space Division announced Thursdayhas a potential value of more than $250 million. The amount ATandamp;Twill receive from ABC was not disclosed at the request of itsparent, Capital Cities-ABC Inc.   GE will build three Telstar 4 satellites, and there is an optionfor a fourth, ATandamp;T said. One will be launched in February 1993, onewill be launched in February 1994 and one will be a spare.   ABC said it was the first television network to commit to buyspace on ``the next generation of satellites.''</TEXT></DOC>